  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct used in posterior lumbar spinal fixation. The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed; one factor (Test conditions) falls below the required level due to evaluation under a single loading condition. The intended use is limited to pre-market submission support for Class II posterior spinal fixation devices under quasi-static compressive-bending loads per ASTM F1717. This package conforms to ProfileMinimal; structured context-of-use linkage is deferred to the prose Claim and Requirement nodes.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/f1717-compression-bending-fea-accuracy",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/claim/fea-predicts-f1717-construct-stiffness-within-10pct",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/model/pedicle-screw-fea-ensemble-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/f1717-experimental-n11-lab1",
    "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/f1717-experimental-n11-lab2"
  ],
